Once the Gruthungi, hewing down a forest to make them boatS, dared to pass beyond the Danube. Three thousand vesseIS‚ each crowded with a barbarous crew, made a dash across the river. Odothaeus was their leader. Thy youth, nay, the first year of thy life, crushed the attempt of that formidable fleet. Its boats filled and sank; never did the fish of that northern river feed more lavishly on the bodies of men. The island of Peuce was heaped high with corpses, Scarce even through five mouths could the river rid itself of barbarian blood, and thy sire, owning thine influence, gave thanks to thee for the spoils won in person from King Odothaeus, Consul a second time thou didst end civil war by thine auspiceS.
